---
export const updateMeta = {
  date: '2026-05-25',
  title: 'Mobile-app return bridges for Stripe Connect + listing payment',
  tags: ['mobile', 'stripe', 'deep-links'],
};
---
<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">May 25, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">
    Added three tiny bridge pages so the BreederHQ mobile app reliably
    returns from Stripe Connect onboarding and listing-fee Checkout.
  </p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
    <strong>New routes:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 list-disc ml-6 mt-2">
    <li><code>/provider/stripe-connect/return</code></li>
    <li><code>/provider/stripe-connect/refresh</code></li>
    <li><code>/provider/listings/[id]/payment/return</code> (SSR)</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-3">
    Each page is noindex, has no Layout, and immediately redirects to the
    matching <code>breederhq://</code> custom-scheme deep link. Required
    because Stripe's in-app browser (SFSafariViewController / Chrome
    Custom Tabs) does not honor Universal Links the same way native
    Safari does — without these pages, completing Stripe onboarding from
    the mobile app returns to <code>breederhq.com/...</code> and 404s
    instead of reopening the app. The paths were already declared in the
    AASA file for the Safari-native case.
  </p>
</article>
